claim.claim-text:
A method of manufacturing an electrical wire connection structure in which an electrical wire is crimp-connected to an electrical wire connection portion of a crimp terminal comprising a fitting portion at a tip thereof and the electrical wire connection portion at a rear end thereof, comprising the steps of:
forming the electrical wire connection portion in a tubular shape;
crushing a tip of the tube so that the tip is superimposed and closed;
forming the fitting portion so that the fitting portion is bent integrally with the superimposed and closed portion while containing the superimposed and closed portion.
